
TY  - JOUR
T1  - Dynamic Capabilities and Their Characteristic Qualities: Insights from a Lab Experiment
AU  - Wollersheim, Jutta
AU  - Heimeriks, Koen H.
Y1  - 2016/03/01
PY  - 2016
DA  - 2016/03/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/orsc.2016.1053
DO  - 10.1287/orsc.2016.1053
T2  - Organization Science
JF  - Organization Science
JO  - Organization Science
SP  - 233
EP  - 248
VL  - 27
IS  - 2
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - Despite the prominence of dynamic capabilities in the strategy and organization literatures, we still lack an empirically grounded understanding of the construct. Featuring an extended version of an established card game, our study uses an experiment to induce dynamic capabilities in the laboratory. Our findings reveal that (a) more efficient use of resources, (b) increasing efficiency of coordination, (c) reliance on more appropriate action sequences, and (d) greater deliberation in action are characteristic qualities of dynamic capabilities. Beyond empirically identifying dynamic capabilities, we offer implications for dynamic capabilities and transfer theory.
AB  - Despite the prominence of dynamic capabilities in the strategy and organization literatures, we still lack an empirically grounded understanding of the construct. Featuring an extended version of an established card game, our study uses an experiment to induce dynamic capabilities in the laboratory. Our findings reveal that (a) more efficient use of resources, (b) increasing efficiency of coordination, (c) reliance on more appropriate action sequences, and (d) greater deliberation in action are characteristic qualities of dynamic capabilities. Beyond empirically identifying dynamic capabilities, we offer implications for dynamic capabilities and transfer theory.
